Social Media Do’s and Don’ts Checklist 
Do’s    
• Use a professional profile name and profile picture.  
• Share educational, technical, and positive content.  
• Respect others while commenting or posting.  
• Protect your personal information and privacy settings.  
• Use social media for learning, networking, and career growth.  
• Verify information before sharing it online.  
• Maintain polite and professional communication.  
Don’ts   
• Do not post offensive, abusive, or inappropriate content.  
• Do not share personal details like phone number, address, or passwords.  
• Do not spread fake news or unverified information.  
• Do not use social media during classes or important academic work.  
• Do not engage in cyberbullying or online arguments.  
• Do not post negative comments about college, teachers, or companies.  
• Do not click on suspicious links or unknown messages.
